This repository consists of my php learning.

Below are some key PHP features I have explored and implemented in this repository:

Dynamic Content Generation:

Creating dynamic web pages with PHP and embedding HTML within scripts.

Form Handling:

Processing user input securely through GET and POST methods.

Database Interaction:

Connecting to MySQL databases using PDO and MySQLi.

Executing CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations.

Session Management:

Implementing user authentication and session tracking.

Object-Oriented Programming (OOP):

Utilizing classes, objects, inheritance, interfaces, and traits to write reusable and maintainable code.

Error Handling:

Using try-catch blocks and custom error handlers for robust application development.

File Handling:

Reading, writing, and uploading files securely.

Security Best Practices:

Preventing common vulnerabilities such as SQL injection, XSS (Cross-Site Scripting), and CSRF (Cross-Site Request Forgery).

PHP Frameworks:

Working with popular frameworks like Laravel and CodeIgniter to speed up development and enforce best practices.

APIs and Web Services:

Consuming RESTful APIs and building custom APIs with JSON data.

